{
  "texts": [
    "These findings confirm that water near the functionalized silica surface is oriented differently depending on the surface chemistry, which should have implications for interfacial phenomena.",
    "It is important to note that the observed asymmetry in the distributions stems from the single-interface configuration of our system, where water is present only above the substrate.",
    "This results in an asymmetric distribution of orientations, in contrast to the symmetric curves reported by Wang et al.",
    "98 for confined water in nanoporous silicon.",
    "The deviation from symmetry is also evident in the film case (see the lower snapshot in Figure 17), where the water/vacuum interface (with vacuum positioned below) yields a similar asymmetric trend."
  ]
}